{
  "doc_id": "3379",
  "text": "The mean serum zinc concentration reported in the present study is consistent with other reports, including levels in young women of childbearing age [CITATION_1] , a study in a general French adult population [CITATION_2] , and concentrations were higher than those reported in omnivores and vegetarians [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Factors that may decrease plasma zinc include vegetarian diets, where as much as 35% of a reduction in plasma zinc is reported [CITATION_5] . Despite the association between zinc and iron, only a weak negative correlation was seen between serum zinc concentrations and STfR but not with other biomarkers of iron status.",
